Ole Andreas Halvorsen (born 1961) is a Norwegian-born investor, hedge fund manager, and philanthropist. He is the CEO and a co-founder of the Connecticut-based hedge fund, Viking Global Investors.[3] Viking had $16.7 billion under management as of April 2012.[4] Halvorsen has consistently ranked among the top earning hedge fund managers, placing 11th in Forbes' 2012 rankings and 9th in 2015, according to Institutional Investor's Alpha.[5][6][7]
Halvorsen is a protégé of hedge fund manager Julian Robertson.[8]



