Biography
Halvorsen graduated from the Norwegian Naval Academy and served on the Norwegian Seal team in the Royal Norwegian Navy. Started his career with Morgan Stanley, where he served in the investment banking division and mergers and acquisitions department. In 1992, joined Tiger Management Corporation, a hedge fund started by investor Julian Robertson. Served as a Senior Managing Director. In 1999, Halvorsen co-founded a hedge fund, Viking Global Investors, with two other Tiger Management employees, David Ott and Brian Olson. Between 1999 to 2005, Halvorsen ...
