Philanthropy

Giving Profile: Serves as a Trustee of the Halvorsen Family Foundation. In 2015, the foundation had assets exceeding $120 million and donated more than $300,000; gives primarily to education, sports, environment and social causes. Recipients include: Green Mountain Valley School, Greenwich Academy, New Canaan Country School, Stanford Graduate School of Business, Williams College, Stowe Land Trust and Stiftelsen Nye Heminghallen. Also serves as a Director of the Viking Global Foundation. In 2015, the foundation had assets exceeding $3 million and donated more than $2 million. Recipients include: Family Centers, Brooklyn Kindergarten Society, All Our Kin, Child First, Research Foundation of Cuny, United Way and Hudson Guild. Halvorsen has donated with his wife to various organizations including, Museum of Modern Art (MOMA), Community Fund of Darien, Teach For America and Right to Play.

