Background

		Mr. Ole Andreas Halvorsen is the Chief Executive Officer at Viking Global Investors LP. Mr. Halvorsen co-founded the firm in 1999. Prior to this, he was a Senior Managing Director, Director of Equities, Analyst, and Member of Advisory Board at Tiger Management Corp. Before that, Mr. Halvorsen was an investment banker in the corporate finance and merger departments at Morgan Stanley. He served as a Platoon Commander on the Norwegian Seal Team. Mr. Halvorsen is a Member ... of the Advisory Council of Stanford Graduate School of Business. He received his M.B.A. from the Stanford Graduate School of Business in 1990, where Mr. Halvorsen was an Arjay Miller Scholar and received the Alexander A. Robichek Award. He graduated from Williams College in 1986. Mr. Halvorsen graduated from Sjøkrigsskolen i Bergen.Read Full Background




